        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 3:56PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from Edroy to near Robstown. Movement was northeast at 25
mph. Wind gusts up to 49 mph have been observed just north of
Robstown.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Driscoll, Portland, North San Pedro, Corpus Christi North Beach,
Sinton, Edroy, Petronila, Gregory, Woodsboro, Bonnie View, Clarkwood,
Annaville, Ingleside On The Bay, Calallen, Del Mar College Windward
Campus, Ingleside, Taft Southwest, Corpus Christi International
Airport, Cole Park, and Driscoll Childrens Hospital.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 37 between mile markers 1 and 24.
US Highway 181 between mile markers 618 and 648.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 630 and 678.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
